results.name: Prime(m), where m is such that (Sum_{i=1..m} prime(i)^3) / m is an integer.
link: OEIS Wiki, Sums of powers of primes divisibility sequences
example: a(2) = 97, because 97 is the 25th prime and the sum of the first 25 primes^3 = 4696450 when divided by 25 equals 187858 which is an integer.
mathematica: k = 1; p = 2; s = 0; lst = {}; While[p < 1000000000, s = s + p^3; If[ Mod[s, k++] == 0, AppendTo[lst, p]]; p = NextPrime@ p]; lst
xref: Cf. A085450 (smallest m > 1 that divides Sum_{k=1..m} prime(k)^n.
